---
import "../styles/global.css";
import DocsLayout from "../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
import styles from "./index.module.css";
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Arris Documentation"
  breadcrumbs={[{ label: "Docs" }]}
  heading="Arris Documentation"
  lede="A modern Data IDE, built for the modern data team."
  tocItems={[
    { label: "Welcome", href: "#welcome" },
    { label: "Sections", href: "#sections" },
  ]}
  currentPath="/"
  next={{ label: "Install Arris", href: "/getting-started/install", section: "Getting started" }}
>
  <h2 id="welcome">Welcome</h2>

  <p>
    Arris is a desktop data workbench for working with all the most popular database engines. Unlike
    many database clients that lean heavily on the JVM and consume large amounts of memory, Arris is
    built on a Rust backend with Rust-based drivers, keeping the IDE lightweight and fast.
  </p>

  <p>
    And it is more than a database client: beyond writing SQL with dialect-aware autocomplete, you can
    join data across different databases with the DataFusion engine, work with dbt and SQLMesh
    through first-class support, run Python and Jupyter, and visualize query results, with more to
    discover as we keep improving.
  </p>

  <p>
    New in this release: the <a href="/canvas">Canvas</a>, a board where you describe an analysis in
    plain English and an AI agent builds it for you, the query, the chart, and the explanation, all
    laid out together.
  </p>

  <p>
    This documentation covers everything from installing the app and running your first query to
    advanced topics like cross-source federation, analytics engineering workflows, and configuring
    AI providers. Use the sidebar to navigate, or pick a section below to get started.
  </p>

  <h2 id="sections">Sections</h2>

  <div class={styles.grid}>
    <a href="/getting-started/install" class={styles.card}>
      <div class={styles.cardTitle}>
        <span class={styles.cardIcon} class:list={["bg-accent-tint text-accent-2"]}>1</span>
        Getting started
      </div>
      <div class={styles.cardDesc}>Install Arris, connect to your first database, and run a query in under two minutes.</div>
      <div class={styles.cardCount}>4 articles</div>
    </a>

    <a href="/connections/overview" class={styles.card}>
      <div class={styles.cardTitle}>
        <span class={styles.cardIcon} class:list={["bg-[rgba(106,161,255,0.15)] text-db-postgres"]}>2</span>
        Connections
      </div>
      <div class={styles.cardDesc}>Add and manage connections to every supported database engine.</div>
      <div class={styles.cardCount}>8 articles</div>
    </a>

    <a href="/supported-data-sources/bigquery" class={styles.card}>
      <div class={styles.cardTitle}>
        <span class={styles.cardIcon} class:list={["bg-[rgba(255,209,102,0.15)] text-yellow"]}>3</span>
        Supported data sources
      </div>
      <div class={styles.cardDesc}>Connection guides for every supported engine: BigQuery, ClickHouse, DuckDB, Postgres, Snowflake, MongoDB, and more.</div>
      <div class={styles.cardCount}>17 articles</div>
    </a>

    <a href="/canvas" class={styles.card}>
      <div class={styles.cardTitle}>
        <span class={styles.cardIcon} class:list={["bg-[rgba(195,155,255,0.15)] text-accent-2"]}>4</span>
        Canvas
      </div>
      <div class={styles.cardDesc}>New: a board where an AI agent turns a plain-English request into a running query, a chart, and the text that explains it.</div>
      <div class={styles.cardCount}>1 article</div>
    </a>

    <a href="/querying/editor" class={styles.card}>
      <div class={styles.cardTitle}>
        <span class={styles.cardIcon} class:list={["bg-[rgba(122,220,228,0.15)] text-teal"]}>5</span>
        Querying
      </div>
      <div class={styles.cardDesc}>The editor, the results viewer with charts, and the session command logs.</div>
      <div class={styles.cardCount}>3 articles</div>
    </a>

    <a href="/querying/cross-source" class={styles.card}>
      <div class={styles.cardTitle}>
        <span class={styles.cardIcon} class:list={["bg-[rgba(195,155,255,0.15)] text-accent-2"]}>6</span>
        Federation
      </div>
      <div class={styles.cardDesc}>Query multiple databases in one SQL statement, powered by the built-in DataFusion engine.</div>
      <div class={styles.cardCount}>3 articles</div>
    </a>

    <a href="/git/version-control" class={styles.card}>
      <div class={styles.cardTitle}>
        <span class={styles.cardIcon} class:list={["bg-[rgba(255,107,107,0.15)] text-red"]}>7</span>
        Git
      </div>
      <div class={styles.cardDesc}>Track changes to your SQL files with built-in Git support: stage, commit, push, and view diffs without leaving Arris.</div>
      <div class={styles.cardCount}>1 article</div>
    </a>

    <a href="/analytics-engineering/dbt" class={styles.card}>
      <div class={styles.cardTitle}>
        <span class={styles.cardIcon} class:list={["bg-[rgba(91,227,154,0.15)] text-green"]}>8</span>
        Analytics engineering
      </div>
      <div class={styles.cardDesc}>Work with dbt and SQLMesh projects, explore lineage, and run models directly from the editor.</div>
      <div class={styles.cardCount}>3 articles</div>
    </a>

    <a href="/ai/codex-agent" class={styles.card}>
      <div class={styles.cardTitle}>
        <span class={styles.cardIcon} class:list={["bg-[rgba(255,161,74,0.15)] text-orange"]}>9</span>
        AI
      </div>
      <div class={styles.cardDesc}>Chat with a local Codex agent to write, explain, and fix schema-aware SQL (requires a Codex subscription or OPENAI_API_KEY).</div>
      <div class={styles.cardCount}>1 article</div>
    </a>

  </div>
</DocsLayout>
